If you want to manage more push-ups, try doing them on your kneecaps. You have a carpet anyways, so it doesn't hurt as much as it usually would if you are not used to this modified exercise. However, it does help with shoulder and back strength and obviously also strengthens your knees, both of which is needed if you have a job where you're on your feet a lot.
